metadata.name: Not A World
metadata.description:
Meet here a collection of tiny procedural worlds generated with a random noise. Each planet is different, with random matching colors, based on the height of the different vertices. 
 There are 3 levels of rarity : Common, Rare, Legendary.

This is a ThreeJS experience, with custom shaders, post-processing, many random parameters, and a lot of love. Everything is handled by the GPU to increase performances and give you a better mint.

There are 365 iterations, based on the revolution period of the Earth, but remember, this is not a world. The price will give you a hint.

metadata.name: Genome hash Analysis
metadata.description:
+ VisualArt based on your unique fxhash as an output.

Every mint gets an analysis of its genome, using as seed the alphanumeric string that makes up its unique hash.



Features

Random Number:
It is the variable corresponding to fxrand()

NFT-HashSeed: 
All the numbers that make up the alphanumeric hash are added, to generate the seed from those unique values.

Color Palette Group:
There are 10 groups corresponding to the color palette, which add up to a total of 100 possible combinations.



* Rare variations are created for 50% of the editions.

* Your unique hash is translated into a visual genome scan.

metadata.name: spaceplant
metadata.description:
Natural processes are computational at their very core, and like atoms, gravity, electricity, the sun, the moon, and the big bang, computation tells part of our cosmological story.

The "spaceplant" series expresses this "computational beauty of nature" (a phrase borrowed from Gary William Flake's book of that title) through a lo-fi simulated garden. This garden has been grown by collecting, curating and nurturing algorithmic specimens that inhabit a space both cellular and planetary. A symphony of particle forces orchestrates the form and interaction of the simulation, tuned to  cosmological constants by the artist.

49 kB of compiled JavaScript. Code written 100% from scratch with no dependencies. Mouse interactive.

Dutch auction at 18:00 UTC, Mar 4 2020, starting at 80 tez and going down to 15 tez.

metadata.name: Digital Images for Analog Eyes
metadata.description:
An attempt at capturing a uniquely digital aesthetic in code-generated images.
Alternatively this is just experimentation with color, noise and the modulo operator.

Details may vary per device, aspect ratio and window size

Generative images by @0x3739
Visuals are code-generated
library: twgljs - A Tiny WebGL helper Library
License: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0

controls
'-' to zoom in.
'+' to zoom out.
'k' to decompose/pixelize the image.
Can take up to 10 decomposing steps before the effect is visible.
'8' or 'arrow_up' to move up in the image.
'5' or 'arrow_down' to move down in the image.
'6' or 'arrow_right' to move right in the image.
'4' or 'arrow_left' to move left in the image.
'1,f,w,a' to change the aspect ratio.
's' to save an image of the canvas.
'h' to increase the quality modifier (maximum is 5).
'l' to decrease the quality modifier (minimum is 1).
The quality modifier is a modifier on the width and height of the canvas.
Changing the modifier can affect the look of the image due to subpixel artifacts.
Use the modifier to save higher resolution images.

metadata.name: Modular Permutation
metadata.description:
The permutation of sounds and colors tries to understand the natural order of numbers and their forms represented in nature, silence is where that number meets infinity, noise is the movement of air, silence flows like this the chaos of numbers, creating the abstract . this abstract simulation is part of a cultural context and a digital effervescence, where computers are no longer tools and become co-authors in the random factor that simulates chaos in this modular composition, both in image and in sound.

by Marcelo Moura · Brazil, 2022 | GTK:javascript/hydra'ojack Music: vcvrack

metadata.name: NotSoDumbAss
metadata.description:
Donkeys have a well-deserved reputation for obstinacy, which has been attributed to a far stronger sense of self-preservation than other animals. It is much more difficult to compel or frighten a donkey into performing anything it thinks to be harmful for whatever reason, likely due to a stronger prey drive and a lesser bond with people.

NotSoDumbAss is a set of 30 donkey NFTs with a layer of rectangular and circular pixels in a variety of colours overlaid on top.

metadata.name: Psychedelic Bounce
metadata.description:
Psychedelic Bounce re-imagines one of the first graphical video games [Pong] through the lens of a psychedelic experience - complete with persistent tracers, vivid saturated colors and monochromatics, random coloring and banding, changing puck shape with fixed and modulating puck sizes, and drawing with transparency. Psychedelic Bounce pauses drawing every 33 bounces and switches to a super trippy quad symmetry output. When the display is put in fullscreen, the default 1:1 aspect ratio is stretched to fill the screen.

All features can be manipulated interactively using the keyboard.
- Space key or mouse click starts/stops puck drawing
(drawing starts with quad symmetry off: enable with 'q' key)
(stopping drawing turns quad symmetry on: disable with 'q' key)
- 'q' or 'Q' - quad symmetry (on/off)
- 'r' or 'R' - rotate quad symmetry by 90 degrees
- 'p' or 'P' - auto pausing function (on/off)
(pausing turns quad symmetry off: enable with 'q' key)
- 'g' or 'G' - puck shape (square/circle/both)
- 'x' or 'X' - monochrome/full color
(background remain the initial monochrome or full color)
- 'c' or 'C' - select random puck color
- 'a' or 'A' - random color draw every other bounce (on/off)
- 'e' or 'E' - random color on every puck draw
(only works with random color draw every other bounce on)
- 'b' or 'B' - color banding (on/off)
(banding color is complementary color of the puck color)
- 'm' or 'M' - puck modulation (on/off)
- 't' or 'T' - transparency (on/off)
- '1' - slowest (1 fps) puck drawing
- '2' - slower (10 fps) puck drawing
- '3' - faster (30 fps) puck drawing
(fps rate may not be accurate if quad symmetry enabled)
- 's' - save 4000 x 4000 pixel png image with border
- [shift]'S' - save 4000 x 4000 pixel png image without border
(fullscreen saved images are screen dimensions X 2)
- 'n' or 'N' - re-initializes the gentk

Rarity features are written to the console at loading and whenever changed interactively.

March 2022
coded by StreamDreamz (a.k.a. Freakiebeat)
coded with - html, css, javascript, p5.js

License: NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: Telar
metadata.description:
Telar is a study about weaving.

Weaving is one of the oldest crafts in the world. It's been part of our history for almost 30,000 years. 

We are used as species to continuously see patterns generated by millions of binary decisions between colors. These patterns are part of the social DNA of almost every human culture, and their complex aesthetics generated by the most simple inputs are fascinating to me.

This piece, inspired by the mechanism of the Jacquard Loom — which is widely considered the first computer — uses combinations of colors, series, threading, treadling, and tie-up patterns to generate a unique 360-by-360-thread Telar ("loom" in Spanish). 

The algorithm called telar.js uses the hash to select some colors from preselected patterns and uses the input series to generate a base model with a starting pattern. After that, multiple iterations alter the model appending new tie-ups and modifying the threading or treadling and colors while keeping the design consistent. A resulting matrix containing each intersection then gets drawn on the screen resulting in a high-definition image the viewer can zoom in and see in detail. 

This algorithm takes too many pseudorandom trait values as its inputs that naming them was meaningless, so I would prefer collectors to focus on the subjective aesthetic values of the outputs. Therefore I am hiding the features for this collection.

Press 'S' on your keyboard to save it as a 36 megapixels print. Use the arrow keys to flip between the face and the back of the fabric.

metadata.name: Mootux x Salose Scarf
metadata.description:
This is a collaboration between 2 projects on different blockchains,
MOOTUX. FULL-color art. Non-generative. Digitally hand-drawn on Smartphone. 1/1. Inclusively designed to be gender-neutral, expression neutral, and FULL colors to appear fancy across ranges of visual ability.
SALOSE. Salose is home to 1,000 generative arts where An iconic scarf design that can become a symbol of dynamism, tenacity, and strong determination inspired by the iconic building of the Sumenep Grand Mosque.

metadata.name: Glorbz - Juggernaut unit
metadata.description:
Hey there! I've heard you're planning on invading earth, but without an attack force how are you gonna do that? Don't worry friend I've got your back, there's nothing better than an army of Glorbz to help you achieve your goal!
What? You want more? Damn you're really going all-in aren't you? Ok listen here, I'm not supposed to sell it but you've been a great customer and I like you, so let me show you this! I present to you the juggernaut unit, your ultimate trump card to conquer the earth!

Click on the Glorbz to make them shoot!

Play the full game: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/9594
Follow on twitter for more generative games: @mitsuhashish
Chat with the author and get drops: https://discord.gg/TrwmVnc

metadata.name: Stoner Stick People Series 2
metadata.description:
The other day I was finally inspired to pick up the Stoner Stick People and again venture off into places I hadn't been, trying new things. I wanted to do more than I'd done before, a promise to myself, and it took a minute for something to click. Color. Not just little bits, but entire environments, Vibes, for Stoners to just, well, Vibe in. The way I wanted to vibe. Be distracted and free my mind to go to the places where it needed to. Needs to.

Another experiment in learning how to layer and play with...lots, lol. I hope y'all enjoy Series 2 :)

Puff puff pass.

Wessel '22

metadata.name: zero-player stained glass
metadata.description:
After selecting nodes by poisson disc sampling, a voronoi grid was created and cyclic cellular automata were applied to this grid. Unlike the case of applying cyclic celluar automata to the rect grid, the wave does not continue and disappears gradually.

keyboard controls:
[s] - Get an image of 600 x 600 px.
[d] - Get an image of 1200 x 1200 px. (2x magnification)

metadata.name: gridography
metadata.description: gridography is an ink-dot inspired collection, with randomly generated features such as grid density, distortion angle, and distortion amount. The inclusion of red dots is the most notable feature. There is a ~50% chance that there is no dot, and decreasing chances that there are up to 8 red dots.

metadata.name: VANDAL SKULL
metadata.description:
VANDAL SKULL character that is part of the project "DIRTY TOYS" created by Deny in partnership with MadcapStudio.
________

Its a layered .png code with another features in canvas/body for a better experience in full view.
________

Here you can find seven features with a rarity setup for each feature.

► Masks: 5 to 10%
► Smoker mask + molotov item: 5%
► Sunglasses: 10%
► Black Plaid background: 5%
► Army sweatshirt: 5%
► All **golden** itens have only 3% chance to appear

________

For a better preview, try to see in open view.

Press 'S' to save.
________

Art by Deny @madcapstudio
Code by @Kukuti89

metadata.name: Abstraction of Multiverse Rotation
metadata.description:
I can feel my existence in this universe.
But is there another me in another universe?
Are we have met each other?
Maybe he have a better live in there, or it can be worst than my self in here.
But all I know, we can't make a contact.
It can be worst for all of us and the living.
Or maybe you wanna call it?

note: turn on the microphone so you can made a chaos

Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

Ali Azca, 2022
https://linktr.ee/aliazcaa

metadata.name: Deep Dark Roots
metadata.description: Based on chaos, Deep Dark Roots is a procedural way of representing all the paths that darkness can take and all the turns that anger can represent. There is 32 editions, because in Dante's Divine Comedy, the number 32 represents the song of the 9th circle, the one from hell.

metadata.name: Doors to the world
metadata.description:
Greetings gentlemen. This work allows you to see the world from an ideal room and look at it from different angles. You will see how pristine nature differs from iconic historical events. Point at the door and see how strikingly different reality is from what people call the story of the life they live

Hover over a door to open it

metadata.name: Wormhole
metadata.description:
Wormhole is a 3D generative realtime animation where your point of view continuously follows the insides of an hypnotic tunnel formed with color and recursive patterns.

Pattern style names: Checkers, Twister, Hooks, Stripes, Rings, Dots, Zigzag, Clockwork and Staccato.

Created by Mario Carrillo using JavaScript, Threejs and Shaders.
